  "local_port": 35744,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the biggest differences between the Jeep Wrangler trims?",
  "response": "The Jeep Wrangler is available in several trims, each differing in terms of features, capabilities, and pricing. The biggest differences between them typically include performance specifications, off-road capabilities, interior and exterior features, technology, and luxury options. Here\u2019s a general overview of some key Jeep Wrangler trims:\n\n1. **Sport**:\n   - **Engine**: Standard 3.6L V6, optional 2.0L turbocharged 4-cylinder.\n   - **Interior**: Basic features, cloth seats, manual windows and locks.\n   - **Exterior**: Steel wheels, basic exterior design.\n   - **Off-Road Capability**: Solid Dana axles, available Command-Trac 4WD system.\n   - **Technology**: Basic infotainment system, smaller touchscreen.\n\n2. **Sport S**:\n   - **Engine**: Same options as the Sport.\n   - **Interior**: Upgraded features like power windows and locks, optional convenience packages.\n   - **Exterior**: Alloy wheels, additional color options.\n   - **Off-Road Capability**: Similar to Sport, with available upgrades.\n   - **Technology**: Enhanced infotainment options, available larger touchscreen.\n\n3. **Sahara**:\n   - **Engine**: Same engine options, but can include additional powertrain combinations like mild hybrid systems.\n   - **Interior**: More refined with additional comfort features, leather seats optional.\n   - **Exterior**: Body-colored fender flares, premium wheels, more sophisticated styling.\n   - **Off-Road Capability**: Full-time Selec-Trac 4WD available.\n   - **Technology**: More advanced infotainment system, larger touchscreen, premium audio systems.\n\n4. **Rubicon**:\n   - **Engine**: Same engine options, highlighted for off-road prowess.\n   - **Interior**: Durable and designed for off-road adventures, premium options.\n   - **Exterior**: Off-road oriented components like rock rails, increased clearance, aggressive styling.\n   - **Off-Road Capability**: Enhanced with Rock-Trac 4WD system, electronic locking differentials, sway bar disconnect, reinforced axles.\n   - **Technology**: Similar to Sahara but often includes off-road specific features.\n\n5. **Unlimited** (Extended wheelbase variant):\n   - **Engine**: Same options, reflects the specific trim such as Sport, Sahara, Rubicon.\n   - **Interior**: More spacious, additional legroom and cargo space.\n   - **Exterior**: Extended wheelbase, can carry more gear.\n   - **Off-Road Capability, Technology**: Dependent on specific trim.\n\n6. **High Altitude**:\n   - **Engine**: High-end versions of standard options.\n   - **Interior**: Luxury-focused, high-quality materials, advanced comfort features.\n   - **Exterior**: Sleek design elements, larger premium wheels, body-colored bumpers.\n   - **Off-Road Capability**: Designed more for road comfort with some off-road capabilities.\n   - **Technology**: Top-tier infotainment and connectivity options.\n\nEach trim is designed to cater to different needs, from basic functionality and cost-efficiency to enhanced off-road performance and luxury. The choice ultimately depends on individual preferences, intended usage, and budget.",
